  "title": "La Rochefoucauld §laroch_008: The passions are the only advocates which always persuade.",
  "body": "The passions are the only advocates which always persuade. They are a natural art, the rules of which are infallible; and the simplest man with passion will be more persuasive than the most eloquent without. [See Maxim 249 which is an illustration of this.]",
